"**Max Boot Environments:** |trueos| automatically creates a boot environment"
" before updating any software, the operating system, or applying a system "
"update. Once the configured maximum number of boot environments is reached, "
"|trueos| will automatically prune (delete) the oldest automatically created "
"boot environment. However, it will not delete any boot environments created "
"manually using :ref:`Boot Environment Manager`. The default number of boot "
"environments is *5*, with an allowable range from *1* to *10*."
