#: ../../sysadmclient.rst:1048
msgid ""
"A snapshot provides a \"point-in-time\" image of the ZFS pool. This is "
"similar to a full system backup as the snapshot contains the information for"
" the entire filesystem. However, it has several advantages over a full "
"backup. Snapshots occur instantaneously, meaning the filesystem does not "
"need to be unmounted and you can continue to use applications on your system"
" as the snapshot is created. Since snapshots contain the meta-data ZFS uses "
"to access files, the snapshots themselves are small and subsequent snapshots"
" only contain the changes that occurred since the last snapshot was taken. "
"This space efficiency means you can take snapshots often. Snapshots also "
"provide a convenient way to access previous versions of files as you can "
"browse to the point-in-time for the version of the file you need. Life "
"Preserver makes it easy to configure when snapshots are taken and provides a"
" built-in graphical browser for finding and restoring the files within a "
"snapshot."
msgstr ""

#: ../../sysadmclient.rst:1255
